org.apache.ambari.server.controller.internal

Class RequestOperationLevel

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.apache.ambari.server.controller.internal.RequestOperationLevel

  • public class RequestOperationLevel
extends Object
    Operation level is specified along with some requests. It identifies the logical level, at which the operation is executed.

      • propertiesFor

        public static Map<String,String> propertiesFor(Resource.Type type,
                                               String clusterName)
        Create a map of required properties to be added to a request info map which is then used to create a RequestOperationLevel object. Other properties (service name, host name, host component name) can be set on the request info map itself as needed.
        Parameters:
        type - resource type for which to calculate the operation level
        clusterName - cluster name
        Returns:
        immutable map with required properties: operation level and cluster name
        Throws:
        IllegalArgumentException - if the given resource type is not mapped to any operation level
